Valentine, 1932b: 2. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="40C222D31ADB770372AC849F99213724" authorityName="Valentine" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Horologion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="459" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speokoites">
<emphasis id="DD22355F0F87D4DB5959A32776CF0454" italics="true" pageId="459" pageNumber="460">Horologion speokoites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Valentine, 1932 by monotypy. Etymology (original). From the Greek 
<emphasis id="D6DA844C58AEB29CDF8C89E0C0EBA419" italics="true" pageId="459" pageNumber="460">horologion</emphasis>
(hourglass), probably alluding to the shape of the body of the adult which, because of the markedly constricted pronotum posteriorly, resembles an hourglass [neuter].
</paragraph>
